In [10]:
# RM 
from sklearn.linear_model import RANSACRegressor

ransac = RANSACRegressor(LinearRegression(), 
                         max_trials=100, 
                         min_samples=50, 
                         loss='absolute_loss', 
                         residual_threshold=5.0, 
                         random_state=0)
X = df[['RM']].values
y = df['MEDV'].values

ransac.fit(X, y)

inlier_mask = ransac.inlier_mask_
outlier_mask = np.logical_not(inlier_mask)

line_X = np.arange(3, 10, 1)
line_y_ransac = ransac.predict(line_X[:, np.newaxis])
plt.scatter(X[inlier_mask], y[inlier_mask],
            c='steelblue', edgecolor='white', 
            marker='o', label='Inliers')
plt.scatter(X[outlier_mask], y[outlier_mask],
            c='limegreen', edgecolor='white', 
            marker='s', label='Outliers')
plt.plot(line_X, line_y_ransac, color='black', lw=2)   
plt.xlabel('Average number of rooms [RM]')
plt.ylabel('Price in $1000s [MEDV]')
plt.legend(loc='upper left')

plt.show()

print(': %.3f' % ransac.estimator_.coef_[0])
print(': %.3f' % ransac.estimator_.intercept_)

: 10.735
: -44.089

2) Variable Selection¶

2-1) Forward Selection¶

In [16]:
# Forward Selection  
variables = df.columns[:-1].tolist() ##   
 
y = df['MEDV'] ##  
selected_variables = [] ##  
sl_enter = 0.05
 
sv_per_step = [] ##    
adjusted_r_squared = [] ##    
steps = [] ## 
step = 0
while len(variables) > 0:
    remainder = list(set(variables) - set(selected_variables))
    pval = pd.Series(index=remainder) ##  p-value
    ##        
    ##   .
    for col in remainder: 
        X = df[selected_variables+[col]]
        X = sm.add_constant(X)
        model = sm.OLS(y,X).fit()
        pval[col] = model.pvalues[col]
 
    min_pval = pval.min()
    if min_pval < sl_enter: ##  p-value     
        selected_variables.append(pval.idxmin())
        
        step += 1
        steps.append(step)
        adj_r_squared = sm.OLS(y,sm.add_constant(df[selected_variables])).fit().rsquared_adj
        adjusted_r_squared.append(adj_r_squared)
        sv_per_step.append(selected_variables.copy())
    else:
        break

2-2) Backward Selection¶

In [20]:
# Backward Elimination  
variables2 = df.columns[:-1].tolist() ##   
 
y2 = df['MEDV'] ##  
selected_variables2 = variables2 ##     
sl_remove = 0.05
 
sv_per_step = [] ##    
adjusted_r_squared = [] ##    
steps = [] ## 
step = 0
while len(selected_variables2) > 0:
    X = sm.add_constant(df[selected_variables2])
    p_vals = sm.OLS(y,X).fit().pvalues[1:] ##  p-value 
    max_pval = p_vals.max() ##  p-value
    if max_pval >= sl_remove: ##  p-value    
        remove_variable = p_vals.idxmax()
        selected_variables2.remove(remove_variable)
 
        step += 1
        steps.append(step)
        adj_r_squared = sm.OLS(y,sm.add_constant(df[selected_variables2])).fit().rsquared_adj
        adjusted_r_squared.append(adj_r_squared)
        sv_per_step.append(selected_variables.copy())
    else:
        break

2-3) Stepwise Selection¶

In [23]:
# Stepwise Selection  
variables3 = df.columns[:-1].tolist() ##   
 
y = df['MEDV'] ##  
selected_variables3 = [] ##  
sl_enter = 0.05
sl_remove = 0.05
 
sv_per_step = [] ##    
adjusted_r_squared = [] ##    
steps = [] ## 
step = 0
while len(variables) > 0:
    remainder = list(set(variables3) - set(selected_variables3))
    pval = pd.Series(index=remainder) ##  p-value
    ##        
    ##   .
    for col in remainder: 
        X = df[selected_variables3+[col]]
        X = sm.add_constant(X)
        model = sm.OLS(y,X).fit()
        pval[col] = model.pvalues[col]
 
    min_pval = pval.min()
    if min_pval < sl_enter: ##  p-value     
        selected_variables3.append(pval.idxmin())
        ##  
        ##    .
        while len(selected_variables3) > 0:
            selected_X = df[selected_variables3]
            selected_X = sm.add_constant(selected_X)
            selected_pval = sm.OLS(y,selected_X).fit().pvalues[1:] ##  p-value 
            max_pval = selected_pval.max()
            if max_pval >= sl_remove: ##  p-value    
                remove_variable = selected_pval.idxmax()
                selected_variables3.remove(remove_variable)
            else:
                break
        
        step += 1
        steps.append(step)
        adj_r_squared = sm.OLS(y,sm.add_constant(df[selected_variables3])).fit().rsquared_adj
        adjusted_r_squared.append(adj_r_squared)
        sv_per_step.append(selected_variables3.copy())
    else:
        break

3-6) Ridge와 Lasso 비교¶

In [31]:
ridge_result = []
lasso_result = []
alpha = [0.001,0.01,0.1,1,10]

for a in alpha:
  ridge = Ridge(alpha = a)
  lasso = Lasso(alpha = a)

  ridge.fit(xrg_train,yrg_train)
  lasso.fit(xrg_train,yrg_train)

  ridge_y_hat = ridge.predict(xrg_test)
  lasso_y_hat = lasso.predict(xrg_test)

  ridge_r2, lasso_r2 = r2_score(yrg_test,ridge_y_hat), r2_score(yrg_test,lasso_y_hat)
  ridge_result.append(ridge_r2)
  lasso_result.append(lasso_r2)

fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
ax.plot(range(5), ridge_result, '-x', c='blue', label="R2 of Ridge")
ax.plot(range(5), lasso_result, '-x', c='red', label="R2 of Lasso")
plt.xticks(range(5), alpha)
plt.xlabel('alpha')
plt.ylabel('R2')
plt.legend(loc='upper right')
plt.show()

alpha값이 변함에도 Ridge regression은 Robust함을 보인다. 따라서 Ridge regression이 더 적합할것이다.¶

>> 13개의 독립변수들중 임의로 INDUS, RM, AGE, TAX, DIS를 선택하였다.¶

또한 이 5개의 독립변수 모두 Continuous variable이었기에 평균값, 중앙값, 최댓값, 최솟값을 참고하여 categorical variable로 변환하였다. 그리고 p_value를 구해본 결과, 5경우 모두 유의수준 0.05보다 작았기에 영가설을 기각할 수 있으며 종속변수와 각각의 독립변수들에 대해 종속관계라는 대립가설을 채택할수있을것이다.¶
